<subSubSection id="C3196511FA223033FF3F66B54F8D5E83" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBC369AFA223033FF3F66B54E7A5F00" blockId="3.[151,1436,1758,2016]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1438,152,951]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">
The serpentine habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA223034FE7D66B54DEE5BC3" authorityName="Kit Tan &amp; Shuka" authorityYear="2010" box="[469,662,1758,1783]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA223034FE7D66B54DEE5BC3" box="[469,662,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">Tulipa albanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA223034FC3E66B54B675BC3" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[918,1055,1758,1783]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA223034FC3E66B54B675BC3" box="[918,1055,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Radusha (
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA223034FB6B66B54A035BC3" box="[1219,1403,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">locus classicus</emphasis>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F314760AFA223034FF3F676E4E635A2B" box="[151,283,1797,1823]" name="Macedonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA223034FEF5676E4EA75A2A" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[349,479,1797,1822]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA223034FEF5676E4EA75A2A" box="[349,479,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Mirusha region in 
<collectingCountry id="F314760AFA223034FD49676E4C385A2B" box="[737,832,1797,1823]" name="Kosovo" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">Kosovo</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B6BFA223034FC47676E4A515A2B" author="Mayer, E. &amp; Micevski, K." box="[1007,1321,1797,1823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" pagination="591 - 598" refId="ref4923" refString="Mayer, E. &amp; Micevski, K. (1970) Zur Taxonomie und Chorologie von Tulipa scardica Bornm. Feddes Repertorium 80 (7 - 8): 591 - 598." type="journal article" year="1970">Mayer &amp; Micevski (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, plants of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA223034FF3F67474E605A71" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[151,280,1836,1861]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA223034FF3F67474E605A71" box="[151,280,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show great variation in several morphological characters such as leaf form, flower colour, length of filaments and anthers in different parts of its distribution range. Our field and herbarium studies confirm this variation in and between populations. Thus specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA223034FCDC67124C8E5AA6" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[884,1014,1913,1938]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA223034FCDC67124C8E5AA6" box="[884,1014,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Taorska Klisura (collected by Micevski on 
<date id="FFBD105AFA223034FE9867F44EB85A8D" box="[304,448,1951,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" value="1964-05-09">9 May 1964</date>
, SKO) and specimens from Mirusha region (collected by Krasniqi on 
<date id="FFBD105AFA223034FB5167F44AEF5A8D" box="[1273,1431,1951,1977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" value="2002-05-11">11 May 2002</date>
, herb. 
<collectingRegion id="49C7F878FA223034FF7267AD4E4E5AD4" box="[218,310,1990,2016]" country="Kosovo" name="Prishtine" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">Pristina</collectingRegion>
) have flat, slightly undulate leaves and perianth segments with a faint black basal blotch edged pale or bright yellow. The filament colour varies from blackish in Radusha (
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FBB760F34BA85D85" box="[1055,1232,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">locus classicus</emphasis>
) to white or pale purplish in tulips from Mirusha. During our fieldwork to Mirusha region on 
<date id="FFBD105AFA253033FBB460D54BC45DEC" box="[1052,1212,190,216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" value="2010-05-15">15 May 2010</date>
, we have observed plants without any marking on their perianth segments and plants with white basal markings on their perianth. This supports the establishment of four colour forms within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FC3061674B635C11" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[920,1051,268,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FC3061674B635C11" box="[920,1051,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B6BFA253033FB1061674F905C78" author="Mayer, E. &amp; Micevski, K." pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="591 - 598" refId="ref4923" refString="Mayer, E. &amp; Micevski, K. (1970) Zur Taxonomie und Chorologie von Tulipa scardica Bornm. Feddes Repertorium 80 (7 - 8): 591 - 598." type="journal article" year="1970">Mayer &amp; Micevski (1970)</bibRefCitation>
. We consider the recently described 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FD3C61594B1A5C78" authority="Tatic &amp; Krivosej (1997: 733)" authorityName="Tatic &amp; Krivosej" authorityPageNumber="733" authorityYear="1997" box="[660,1122,306,332]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serbica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FD3C61594C7E5C7F" box="[660,774,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. serbica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B6BFA253033FCA661594B1A5C78" author="Tatic, B. &amp; Krivosej, Z." box="[782,1122,306,332]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="733 - 736" refId="ref5177" refString="Tatic, B. &amp; Krivosej, Z. (1997) Tulipa serbica (Liliaceae) a new species from Serbia. Bocconea 5 (2): 733 - 736." type="journal article" year="1997">Tatić &amp; Krivošej (1997: 733)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as falling within the range of variation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FEE761324EAD5C46" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[335,469,345,370]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FEE761324EAD5C46" box="[335,469,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens from Crveni Bregovi-Orlov rid (collected by Micevski on 
<date id="FFBD105AFA253033FA9661324FAE5CAE" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" value="1965-05-20">20 May 1965</date>
, SKO) have undulate leaves and flowers with a distinct black basal blotch within and superficially resemble red-flowered forms of 
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FDB961CC4DE35CF4" box="[529,667,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FDB961CC4DEF5CF4" authorityName="Kit Tan &amp; Shuka" authorityYear="2010" box="[529,663,423,448]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanica">T. albanica</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but the latter can easily be distinguished by the complete absence of a black basal blotch on its perianth segments. It is noteworthy that golden-yellow flowers, which are predominant in 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FEFE619F4EA45F39" authorityName="Kit Tan &amp; Shuka" authorityYear="2010" box="[342,476,500,525]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FEFE619F4EA45F39" box="[342,476,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. albanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(comprising more than 80% of the population), have never been observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FA2E619F4F835F07" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FA2E619F4F835F07" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC369AFA253033FF6E622A4F8D5E83" blockId="4.[151,1438,152,951]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
As in 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FEB9622A4EB25F6E" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[273,458,577,602]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FEB9622A4EB25F6E" box="[273,458,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Tulipa scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, variation in the colour of the perianth and stamens has also been observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FA2E622A4E7B5FB5" authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1873" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schrenkii">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FA2E622A4E7B5FB5" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. schrenkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
native to the steppes and semi-desert areas of 
<collectingCountry id="F314760AFA253033FC9862034CFE5FB6" box="[816,902,616,642]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F314760AFA253033FC3A62034CBC5FB6" box="[914,964,616,642]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Iran</collectingCountry>
, the Caucasus, Daghestan, 
<collectingCountry id="F314760AFA253033FAA262034AEF5FB6" box="[1290,1431,616,642]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, Azarbaijan, western Siberia and the 
<collectingCountry id="F314760AFA253033FDF962E54DC95F9C" box="[593,689,654,680]" name="Ukraine" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B6BFA253033FD6A62E54CC55F9C" author="Botschantzeva, Z. P." box="[706,957,654,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" refId="ref4465" refString="Botschantzeva, Z. P. (1982) Tulips: taxonomy, morphology, cytology, phytogeography and physiology. Rotterdam, Netherlands: Balkema, 227 pp." type="book" year="1982">Botschantzeva 1982</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FC5C62E44B045F9C" authorityName="Kit Tan &amp; Shuka" authorityYear="2010" box="[1012,1148,655,680]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FC5C62E44B045F9C" box="[1012,1148,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. albanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we have only observed yellow and red flower forms and the stamen colour is always constant regardless of perianth colour, i.e., the filaments are always golden-yellow and the anthers dark blackish-maroon (
<figureCitation id="13382A1FFA253033FBBF62B74B0E5FC2" box="[1047,1142,732,758]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[302,1284,429,1510]" captionTargetId="figure-250@3.[302,1284,429,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Tulipa albanica: A: habit. B: flower of yellow form. C: stamens, ovary, stigma of yellow and red-flowered forms. D: capsule and seeds (enlarged). E: bulb. Bar scale 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4899699/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FB2462B74A3F5FC1" authorityName="Kit Tan &amp; Shuka" authorityYear="2010" box="[1164,1351,732,757]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FB2462B74A3F5FC1" box="[1164,1351,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Tulipa albanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FF7063694E225E2F" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[216,346,770,795]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FF7063694E225E2F" box="[216,346,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FE3D63694D675E2F" authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1873" box="[405,543,770,795]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schrenkii">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FE3D63694D675E2F" box="[405,543,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. schrenkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its canaliculate, strongly undulate lower leaves, the upper leaves with a long-tapering apex (
<figureCitation id="13382A1FFA253033FE2A63424EB05E77" box="[386,456,809,835]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1073,1097]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,155,1050]" captionTargetId="figure-283@5.[152,1434,155,1050]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leaves: A: Tulipa albanica, canaliculate and strongly undulate. B: T. scardica, flat, weakly undulate. C: T. schrenkii, flat, not or weakly undulate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4899703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4899703/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and the absence of a black basal blotch on the perianth segments. From 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FAB463424AE45E76" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[1308,1436,809,834]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FAB463424AE45E76" box="[1308,1436,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it additionally differs by its golden-yellow (not whitish or blackish) filaments, smaller capsules and larger seeds. Selected morphological characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FD0F631C4C1A5EA4" authorityName="Kit Tan &amp; Shuka" authorityYear="2010" box="[679,866,887,912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FD0F631C4C1A5EA4" box="[679,866,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Tulipa albanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FCDA631C4C8D5EA4" authorityName="Bornmuller" authorityYear="1923" box="[882,1013,887,912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scardica">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FCDA631C4C8D5EA4" box="[882,1013,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. scardica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D19FA253033FB87631C4BC05EA4" authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1873" box="[1071,1208,887,912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Tulipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schrenkii">
<emphasis id="B977EA88FA253033FB87631C4BC05EA4" box="[1071,1208,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">T. schrenkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are summarized in 
<tableCitation id="C6810321FA253033FF3F63F64F975E83" box="[151,239,925,951]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,241,1002,1026]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological differences between Tulipa albanica, T. scardica and T. schrenkii." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF7C6612FA253033FF3F63814B015935" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" tableUuid="DF7C6612FA253033FF3F63814B015935">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
